{"ts":"2026-06-27T23:02:15.613Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"zbbwgvt9","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Platform: Final MVP Handoff Documentation\n  2 | \n  3 | This document serves as the concise, practical handoff guide for deploying, running, and managing the **GFF AI Platform** (Next.js Frontend & FastAPI Backend).\n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## 1. Product Scope & Architectural Boundaries\n  8 | \n  9 | ### 1.1. Core Platform Components\n 10 | The GFF AI Platform is composed of two primary layers:\n 11 | 1. **Next.js Frontend (App Router)**: A premium, Apple-like web interface providing client portals, administrator portals, public/educational pages, and interactive builders.\n 12 | 2. **FastAPI Backend (REST API)**: A lightweight, high-performance API server managing authentication (JWT), role-based access control (RBAC), multi-tenant data structures, and dashboard operations.\n 13 | \n 14 | ### 1.2. Crucial Scope Notice: GFF AI Tools\n 15 | > ⚠️ **IMPORTANT DESIGN BOUNDARY**:\n 16 | > All interactive **GFF AI Tools** inside the Build suite are **frontend-only, client-side mock configurations and interactive visual flows**. They are explicitly decoupled from the backend and do not call real live AI models, compile real local scripts, or connect to database persistence.\n 17 | > \n 18 | > These include:\n 19 | > *   **Sandbox / Agent Playgrounds** (`/build/sandbox`)\n 20 | > *   **Blueprint Generator** (`/build/blueprint`)\n 21 | > *   **ROI Calculator** (`/build/roi`)\n 22 | > *   **Proposal Builder / Intake** (`/build/proposal`)\n 23 | > *   **Agent Marketplace** (`/build/marketplace`)\n 24 | > *   **AI Readiness Assessment Framework** (`/build/assessment`)\n 25 | > *   **Foundry Studio** (`/build/foundry-studio`)\n 26 | > *   **Interactive Assistant / Talk** (`/build/talk`)\n 27 | >\n 28 | > All backend API integrations are reserved strictly for operational telemetry: User Profile Management, Client Workspace Handshakes, Multi-Tenant Projects, Real-Time Invoices/Epoch Telemetry, Support Ticket Queueing, S3 Document Metadata, and Compliance Governance Controls.\n 29 | \n 30 | ---\n 31 | \n 32 | ## 2. Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure\n 33 | \n 34 | To transition from local SQLite development to production, the backend is engineered for a cloud-native AWS serverless topology (FastAPI on AWS Lambda/ECS connected to DynamoDB and S3).\n 35 | \n 36 | ### 2.1. DynamoDB Data Modeling (Exactly 3 Tables)\n 37 | Complex relational mappings are collapsed into a high-performance single-table design for operational workspace items (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`), alongside dedicated identity tables.\n 38 | \n 39 | | Table Name | Partition Key (PK) | Sort Key (SK) | Global Secondary Index (GSI) | Purpose |\n 40 | | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n 41 | | **`GFF_USERS`** | `email` (String) | *None* | *None* | Global user credentials, roles, and client ties. |\n 42 | | **`GFF_CLIENTS`** | `client_id` (String) | *None* | *None* | Enterprise customer entity directory. |\n 43 | | **`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`** | `PK` (String) | `SK` (String) | `GSI1` (`GSI1PK` & `GSI1SK`) | Multi-tenant single-table workspace store. |\n 44 | \n 45 | #### Single-Table Entity Schema mappings (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`)\n 46 | 1. **Projects**:\n 47 |    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>`\n 48 |    * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `METADATA`\n 49 | 2. **AI Operations (Telemetry)**:\n 50 |    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n 51 |    * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n 52 | 3. **Documents Metadata**:\n 53 |    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n 54 |    * **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n 55 | 4. **Invoices / Billing**:\n 56 |    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n 57 |    * **`GSI1PK`**: `BILLING_PERIOD#<year_month>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n 58 | 5. **Support Tickets**:\n 59 |    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n 60 |    * **`GSI1PK`**: `STATUS#<status_code>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n 61 | 6. **Governance / Controls**:\n 62 |    * **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>` | **`SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n 63 |    * **`GSI1PK`**: `STANDARD#<compliance_standard>` | **`GSI1SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n 64 | \n 65 | ### 2.2. Secure Object Storage (Amazon S3)\n 66 | *   **Bucket Name**: `gff-portal-documents-prod`\n 67 | *   **Access Paradigm**: Block All Public Access. Enforces Server-Side Encryption (SSE-KMS) and strict TLS 1.3 transport.\n 68 | *   **Operation**: The frontend interacts with files using short-lived (15-minute) secure Pre-signed URLs dynamically generated by the FastAPI backend using AWS SDK (Boto3).\n 69 | \n 70 | ---\n 71 | \n 72 | ## 3. Deployment & Operational Environment Variables\n 73 | \n 74 | ### 3.1. Next.js Frontend Keys (`.env` or `.env.production`)\n 75 | Set these environment variables in your Vercel Dashboard, AWS Amplify Console, or CI/CD Pipeline:\n 76 | \n 77 | | Variable Name | Value / Format | Purpose |\n 78 | | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n 79 | | `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://api.gff.ai/v1` | URL pointing to the FastAPI Gateway/Lambda |\n 80 | | `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` | `production` | Deployment stage / environment tag |\n 81 | | `NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enables upload features on Client Portal |\n 82 | | `NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET_NAME` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Target S3 bucket name |\n 83 | \n 84 | ### 3.2. FastAPI Backend Keys (`backend/.env` or Parameter Store / Secrets Manager)\n 85 | Configure these environment variables inside your hosting container or AWS Lambda:\n 86 | \n 87 | | Variable Name | Value / Format | Purpose |\n 88 | | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n 89 | | `PROJECT_NAME` | `\"GFF AI Enterprise Cloud Engine\"` | API title metadata |\n 90 | | `API_V1_STR` | `\"/api/v1\"` | API prefix path |\n 91 | | `ENVIRONMENT` | `\"production\"` | Set runtime stage |\n 92 | | `CORS_ORIGINS` | `https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai` | Allowed frontend domains (CORS compliance) |\n 93 | | `FRONTEND_BASE_URL` | `https://portal.gff.ai` | Root URL of client-facing portal |\n 94 | | `AWS_REGION` | `us-east-1` (or chosen region) | Target region for DynamoDB and S3 |\n 95 | | `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` | *production_aws_access_key_id* | AWS IAM deployer credentials |\n 96 | | `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` | *production_aws_secret_access_key* | AWS IAM deployer secret |\n 97 | | `DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE` | `GFF_USERS` | DynamoDB user registry table |\n 98 | | `DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE` | `GFF_CLIENTS` | DynamoDB enterprise client registry table |\n 99 | | `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE` | `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` | Multi-tenant operational records store |\n100 | | `DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TYPE_INDEX` | `GSI1` | Global Secondary Index for single-table queries |\n101 | | `S3_DOCUMENTS_BUCKET` | `gff-portal-documents-prod` | Secure client document storage |\n102 | | `S3_DOCUMENTS_PREFIX` | `clients` | File key namespace prefix |\n103 | | `JWT_SECRET` | *cryptographically_secure_256_bit_signature_key* | Cryptographic token signing secret |\n104 | | `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` | `1440` (24 hours) | Token lifespan limit |\n105 | \n106 | ---\n107 | \n108 | ## 4. Seeded MVP Credentials\n109 | \n110 | The database contains exactly **four** seeded user accounts covering the three standard RBAC roles (`gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`).\n111 | \n112 | | Role | Email | Password | Associated Client Tenant | Platform Clearance |\n113 | | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n114 | | **`gff_admin`** | `gff_admin@gff.ai` | `password123` | *None* (Global) | Accesses the Admin Dashboard (`/admin/dashboard`). |\n115 | | **`client_admin`** | `client_admin@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Admin for Tenant 1. Full view/edit of Client Workspace. |\n116 | | **`client_member`** | `client_member@apex.com` | `password123` | `Apex Global Solutions` (ID: 1) | Standard user for Tenant 1. Operational-only workspace rights. |\n117 | | **`client_member`** | `client@chevron.com` | `chevron_secure_pass_2026` | `Sovereign Logistics Corp` (ID: 2) | Standard user for Tenant 2. Used to test cross-tenant data isolation. |\n118 | \n119 | ---\n120 | \n121 | ## 5. Execution & Build Commands Reference\n122 | \n123 | ### 5.1. Local Sandbox Environment Execution\n124 | Run these commands from the root of the workspace during local development:\n125 | \n126 | ```bash\n127 | # 1. Install Backend Dependencies (FastAPI, SQLite, SQLite-Utils, Pytest)\n128 | npm run backend:install\n129 | \n130 | # 2. Setup SQLite Schema & Inject Multi-Tenant Seed Users/Items\n131 | npm run backend:seed\n132 | \n133 | # 3. Launch Local Hot-Reloading FastAPI Backend (Standard Port: 8000)\n134 | npm run backend:dev\n135 | \n136 | # 4. Launch Local Hot-Reloading Next.js Frontend (Standard Port: 3000)\n137 | npm run dev\n138 | \n139 | # 5. Run Security, RBAC & End-to-End API Integration Smoke Tests\n140 | npm run backend:check\n141 | ```\n142 | \n143 | ### 5.2. Production Deployment Execution\n144 | Prepare and run production workloads with these instructions:\n145 | \n146 | #### Next.js Frontend Production Build\n147 | To create an optimized production bundle and boot the production web server locally or in a container:\n148 | ```bash\n149 | # Build the application\n150 | npm run build\n151 | \n152 | # Start the node runtime production server\n153 | npm run start\n154 | ```\n155 | \n156 | #### FastAPI Backend Production Launch\n157 | To boot the FastAPI server using multi-threaded Uvicorn workers in cloud hosting VMs, containers, or on-premises servers:\n158 | ```bash\n159 | # Production launch command (4 workers, host bound to all network interfaces)\n160 | uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 4\n161 | ```\n162 | *(For Serverless AWS Lambda deployments, configure API Gateway to route to a Lambda containing the FastAPI application wrapped with the `Mangum` ASGI adapter).*","success":true}],"durationMs":7}}
