d I've listed that all other source code files (especially landing pages or GFF AI tools) should not be touched.\\n\\n\\n**Specifying Infrastructure Deta [line truncated]\n 84 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T22:59:55.946Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"editor\",\"toolCallId\":\"cs01e4bm\",\"input\":{\"path\":\"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\",\"new_text\":\"# GFF AI Platform: Final MVP Handoff Documentation\\n\\nThis document serves as the concise, practical handoff guide for deploying, running, and managing the **GFF AI Platform** (Next.js Frontend & FastAPI Backend).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Product Scope & Architectural Boundaries\\n\\n### 1.1. Core Platform Components\\nThe GFF AI Platform is composed of two primary layers:\\n1. **Next.js Frontend (App Router)**: A premium, Apple-like web interface providing client portals, administrator portals, public/educational pages, and interactive builders.\\n2. **FastAPI Backend (REST API)**: A lightweight, high-performance API server managing authentication (JWT), role-based access control (RBAC), multi-tenant data structures, and dashboard operations.\\n\\n### 1.2. Crucial Scope Notice: GFF AI Tools\\n> ⚠️ **IMPORTANT DESIGN BOUNDARY**:\\n> All interactive **GFF AI Tools** inside the Build suite are **frontend-only, client-side mock configurations and interactive visual flows**. They are explicitly decoupled from the backend and do not call real live AI models, compile real local scripts, or connect to database persistence.\\n> \\n> These include:\\n> *   **Sandbox / Agent Playgrounds** (`/build/sandbox`)\\n> *   **Blueprint Generator** (`/build/blueprint`)\\n> *   **ROI Calculator** (`/build/roi`)\\n> *   **Proposal Builder / Intake** (`/build/proposal`)\\n> *   **Agent Marketplace** (`/build/marketplace`)\\n> *   **AI Readiness Assessment Framework** (`/build/assessment`)\\n> *   **Foundry Studio** (`/build/foundry-studio`)\\n> *   **Interactive Assistant / Talk** (`/build/talk`)\\n>\\n> All backend API integrations are reserved strictly for operational telemetry: User Profile Management, Client Workspace Handshakes, Multi-Tenant Projects, R [line truncated]\n 85 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T22:59:55.948Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"editor\",\"toolCallId\":\"cs01e4bm\",\"output\":{\"query\":\"edit:/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\",\"result\":\"\",\"error\":\"Editor input too large: new_text was 8894 characters, exceeding the recommended limit of 6000. Split the edit into smaller tool calls so later tool calls are less likely to be truncated or time out.\",\"success\":false},\"durationMs\":2}}\n 86 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T22:59:55.949Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"iteration_end\",\"iteration\":8,\"hadToolCalls\":true,\"toolCallCount\":1}}\n 87 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T22:59:55.950Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"iteration_start\",\"iteration\":9}}\n 88 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T22:59:59.034Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Addressing Text Size**\\n\\nI've hit a snag: the editor tool flags the input text as exceeding the character limit. My immediate plan is to handle this either by breaking down the edits into multiple API calls or rewriting smaller chunks at a time. Creating the file with smaller pieces is the next thing on my list.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n 89 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T22:59:59.852Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Refining Chunking Strategy**\\n\\nI'm now focusing on a chunked approach. First, I'll create the file with an initial placeholder or introductory text. I've switched to a strategy that's very efficient and safe: iteratively a