eight, high-performance API server managing authentication (JWT), role-based access control (RBAC), multi-tenant data structures, and dashboard operations.\\n\\n### 1.2. Crucial Scope Notice: GFF AI Tools\\n> ⚠️ **IMPORTANT DESIGN BOUNDARY**:\\n> All interactive **GFF AI Tools** inside the Build suite are **frontend-only, client-side mock configurations and interactive visual flows**. They are explicitly decoupled from the backend and do not call real live AI models, compile real local scripts, or connect to database persistence.\\n> \\n> These include:\\n> *   **Sandbox / Agent Playgrounds** (`/build/sandbox`)\\n> *   **Blueprint Generator** (`/build/blueprint`)\\n> *   **ROI Calculator** (`/build/roi`)\\n> *   **Proposal Builder / Intake** (`/build/proposal`)\\n> *   **Agent Marketplace** (`/build/marketplace`)\\n> *   **AI Readiness Assessment Framework** (`/build/assessment`)\\n> *   **Foundry Studio** (`/build/foundry-studio`)\\n> *   **Interactive Assistant / Talk** (`/build/talk`)\\n>\\n> All backend API integrations are reserved strictly for operational telemetry: User Profile Management, Client Workspace Handshakes, Multi-Tenant Projects, R [line truncated]\n 97 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:02.627Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"editor\",\"toolCallId\":\"dpm698sz\",\"output\":{\"query\":\"edit:/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\",\"result\":\"File created successfully at: /Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md\",\"success\":true},\"durationMs\":2}}\n 98 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:02.627Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"iteration_end\",\"iteration\":9,\"hadToolCalls\":true,\"toolCallCount\":1}}\n 99 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:02.628Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"iteration_start\",\"iteration\":10}}\n100 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:05.997Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Analyzing Infrastructure Deployment**\\n\\nI've confirmed the initial file creation was successful. I'm now focusing on section 2, \\\"Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure,\\\" and reviewing its content, specifically the transition to a production environment using AWS. The backend's design for AWS is the current focus of my analysis.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n101 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:06.918Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Defining Serverless Topology**\\n\\nI'm now zeroing in on the specifics of the proposed AWS infrastructure. The plan is a cloud-native, serverless topology: FastAPI, running on AWS Lambda or ECS, interacting with DynamoDB and S3. My focus is now the DynamoDB data model, specifically the single-table design for workspace items, and I am reviewing it in depth now, considering the three tables (`GFF_USERS`, `GFF_CLIENTS`, `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`) and their keys.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n102 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:08.783Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Examining Data Models**\\n\\nI'm now diving deeper into the single-table DynamoDB design, specifically the data modeling for various workspace items. I'm scrutinizing the Primary Keys (`PK`), Sort Keys (`SK`), and Global Secondary Indexes (GSI) for Telemetry, Documents Metadata, Invoices/Billing, Support Tickets, and Governance/Controls. The structured keys and their relationships are under review. I've also noted that secure object storage is to be maintained using S3, and that the bucket will be named `gff-portal-documents-prod`, with block-all-public-access, server-side encryption, and strict TLS 1.3 transport.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n103 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:09.581Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Evaluating Pre-Signed URLs**\\n\\nI am now assessing the frontend's file interactions, which utilize dynamically generated, 15-minute Pre-signed URLs for secure access. These URLs are created via the FastAPI backend leveraging the AWS SDK (Boto3). This approach's efficiency and security are what I am considering now.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n104 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:11.321Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Reviewing Single-Table Schema**\\n\\nI'm now focusing on the three-table DynamoDB structure. I'm taking a close look at `GFF_USERS`, `GFF_CLIENTS`, and especially `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`, to understand how the tables fit into the high-performance single-table design for workspace items. I'm focusing on the single-table entity schema mappings for projects and AI operations, including partition keys, sort keys, and global secondary indices.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n105 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:12.141Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I will append the \\\"Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure\\\" section using the `editor\",\"accumulated\":\"I will append the \\\"Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure\\\" section using the `editor\"}}\n106 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:12.270Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"text\",\"text\":\"` tool. This segment details the three required DynamoDB tables, the single-table layout, and the S3 bucket configuration.\",\"accumulated\":\"I will append the \\\"Production AWS Cloud Infrastructure\\\" section using the `editor` tool. This segment details the three required DynamoDB tables, the single-table layout, and the S3 bucket configuration.\"}}\n107 | {\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T23:00:15.846Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"usage\",\"inpu